OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F405A1772561166
OL,3,CPlanning approved for #231 million
OL,4,CBarbican Centre renewal
OL,6,FThe wider space will also be improved
OL,7,Fto enable greater programme
OL,8,Fflexibility within the Barbican's
OL,9,Fpublic spaces with the aim of
OL,10,Fexpanding creative opportunities and
OL,11,Fdrawing in new audiences.
OL,13,FChris Hayward, city of London
OL,14,FCorporation policy chairman, said:
OL,15,F"This decision marks a major step
OL,16,Fforward for the Barbican Centre and
OL,17,Fits place on the world stage.
OL,26,@wD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/7
